  "prompt": "I have a Pulsar 200 NS. What would be a good re-placement for 130/70*17 rear tires?",
  "response": "When selecting a replacement tire for your Pulsar 200 NS with a 130/70-17 rear tire size, it's important to consider factors like riding style, terrain, and brand preference. Here are some good options across different categories:\n\n### Sport/Street Tires\n1. **Michelin Pilot Street** - Known for good grip and handling, ideal for urban commuting and occasional spirited rides.\n2. **Pirelli Diablo Rosso II** - Offers excellent grip and performance, suited for more aggressive riding and handling.\n\n### Touring Tires\n1. **Continental ContiGo!** - A balanced option for sport touring with good durability and comfort.\n2. **Dunlop Sportmax Roadsmart III** - Great for long-distance touring with good wet and dry grip.\n\n### Dual-Sport/Adventure Tires\n1. **Metzeler Tourance Next** - If you do a mix of on-road and light off-road, this tire offers versatility and durability.\n2. **Bridgestone Battlax Adventure A41** - Offers excellent performance on both paved and unpaved surfaces.\n\n### Tips for Choosing:\n- **Riding Style**: Choose a tire that matches how you ride (commuting, touring, sport).\n- **Terrain**: Consider where you will be riding most (urban, highway, rough roads).\n- **Brand Preference**: Sticking to reputable brands can ensure better performance and safety.\n\nMake sure to check your local dealers for availability and prices. Always consult with a professional if you're unsure about fitting or suitability.",
